purpose: The commit adds a check in hci_cmd_sync_queue to return -ENODEV if HCI_UNREGISTER flag is set, preventing command queuing that would cause a use-after-free error.
The commit removes an unnecessary header file inclusion to clean up the code.

The commit updates the documentation for the perf c2c tool to reflect a new 'N/A' store metric. This involves modifying the report table in the documentation to include this new metric, which indicates store accesses where memory level information is unavailable.

The commit addresses issues related to vma lock handling during splitting and unmapping in hugetlb. It ensures proper allocation of new locks for duplicated vmas and correctly frees the lock during unmapping, preventing future bugs.

The commit adds documentation for AVDD and MICVDD power supplies in the devicetree bindings for the realtek,rt5682s codec. It updates the YAML file to include descriptions of these supplies, marks them as required, and provides an example usage.
The commit fixes a resource leak by adding an iounmap call in the remove function to handle cases where ioremap must be undone.
The commit removes an unused 'work' field from a structure to improve code quality by eliminating unnecessary elements.

The commit changes the type of key_idx from unsigned to signed in the cfg80211_auth_request struct to avoid static checker warnings when -1 is assigned. This modification prevents potential issues without adding new features or fixing existing bugs.
The commit reorders the CONFIG_SURFACE_PLATFORMS entry in two defconfig files to improve code organization and readability.
The commit introduces a new helper function mcp251xfd_is_fd_mode() and replaces existing checks in multiple files with this function, improving code readability and maintainability.
The commit modifies selftests/rtc/rtctest.c to skip tests when the RTC device is not present, preventing unnecessary test failures.
The commit removes a redundant assignment of 'bytes' which was never used after being reassigned in an if block, addressing a clang build warning about dead code.
The commit decouples rcuscale from RCU Tasks to reduce kernel size and complexity. It modifies Kconfig options and conditional includes in rcuscale.c, as well as updating test configurations.
The commit removes a duplicated phrase in a comment within spte.h, improving the code's documentation.

The commit reverts changes in clock table population for dcn315 clk mgr to prevent underflow issues caused by using dcfclk-based tables when dcfclk states are disabled. It modifies functions related to finding clock values and populating bw_params, improving code structure.

The commit updates the device tree bindings for Mali Bifrost GPUs by adding a compatible string for the Renesas RZ/V2L SoC (R9A07G054) and modifying the schema to include both R9A07G044 and R9A07G054 models.

The commit renames the struct pcie_port to dw_pcie_rp to maintain naming consistency across the DW PCIe core driver entities. This involves modifying multiple files where this struct is declared or used, replacing all instances of pcie_port with dw_pcie_rp.
The commit fixes a Clang -Wformat warning by correcting the format specifier in a debug statement. It changes '06hx' to '06x', ensuring the argument type matches, improving code quality.

This commit fixes an issue in the MIPS architecture where branch offsets were causing warnings due to incorrect range checks. The change involves casting the upper bound of the branch range to a long to handle signed comparisons properly, preventing negative offset issues.
The commit removes the HW_VAR_H2C_FW_P2P_PS_OFFLOAD variable and replaces its usage with direct function calls, part of an effort to eliminate the HAL layer and improve code structure.

The commit modifies the declaration of cavium_erratum_23154_cpus to static const, addressing sparse warnings related to non-global symbols. This change fixes existing build warnings and improves code quality by preventing potential misuse of the symbol.
The commit removes incorrect interrupt flags in MDSS nodes to fix device tree configurations.

The commit refactors how arrays are allocated and managed in struct ctrl_ref, renaming variables from 'dyn' to 'array' for consistency. It prepares for allowing dynamic array size changes from drivers.
The commit adds several PMIC models and SoC entries to the socinfo driver, expanding support for specific hardware platforms.

The commit modifies the chip cut recognition logic to handle all possible values (A-P) instead of defaulting to 'unknown'. It replaces a switch statement with a direct calculation, improving efficiency and correctness.
The commit removes the custom .is_enabled state from PRCMU clocks, aligning with core enable count management and improving code cleanliness.

The commit aims to refactor the code by removing #ifdef CONFIG_XIP_KERNEL usage in various places. It modifies how certain variables and macros are defined, grouping similar cases together to reduce redundancy.
The commit enables QUP and GPI DMA hardware in the device tree to prepare for adding I2C nodes later.
This commit corrects comments in the code, fixes a typo, and adjusts comment formatting to adhere to coding standards. The changes improve code readability and maintainability.

The commit addresses an infinite loop issue in the release_swfw_sync function. It modifies the code to handle cases where acquiring the HW semaphore fails, preventing indefinite hanging and improving error handling.
The commit renames variables and updates comments to use modern ASoC DAI terminology, enhancing code clarity.
The commit removes unnecessary code related to IS_SWAPFILE, which is always defined. This cleanup improves code quality.

The commit implements GTP echo response handling for both GTPv0 and GTPv1u. It adds functions to send Echo Response messages, defines new data structures for these responses, and modifies configuration options to include a restart count. The changes ensure compliance with GTP specifications by correctly formatting and sending Echo Responses when received.
The commit replaces cpumask_next_* functions with cpumask_first_* where appropriate, improving code functionality and adding a new cpumask_first_zero() function.
The commit removes a deprecated function call that was causing errors during roaming by attempting an unsupported operation with firmware.

The commit adds support for a new platform (adl_rt5682) that uses the alc5682 codec without a speaker amplifier. It modifies configuration files in two locations: adding a new entry to board_ids in sof_rt5682.c and adding a new machine definition in soc-acpi-intel-adl-match.c.
The commit adds a check to fail zerocopy sendmsg when the socket does not support it, ensuring proper error handling.

The commit modifies the LaTeX preamble to conditionally load xeCJK.sty only when both the Noto Sans CJK SC font and the style file exist. This prevents errors on systems where these components are missing, such as RHEL 9.
The commit modifies the checkpatch script to stop flagging certain 'case' macros as errors, preventing false positives.

The commit replaces the simpledrm driver's use of simple KMS helpers with atomic helpers. It removes old headers and modifies functions to utilize atomic helper functions for better code structure and maintainability.

The commit adds a JPEG decode worker interface to enable parallel processing of three hardware instances on MT8195. It introduces new functions for managing hardware resources and a worker function for decoding, along with modifications to support multiple HW cores.
The commit removes several VPRINTK() debug calls and the ata_scsi_dump_cdb function, replacing them with tracepoints for better debugging. This improves code cleanliness and efficiency.
This commit adds support for zstate during extended vblank periods, enabling optimization of power usage when in FREESYNC_STATE_VIDEO by utilizing extra vblank time.
The commit corrects a parameter type mismatch in the hqd_destroy callback to fix a CFI failure, ensuring proper function pointer types.
The commit corrects the property name from 'reset' to 'resets' in the device tree bindings for STM32 pinctrl, ensuring proper configuration and adding validation.
The commit modifies the Makefile to suppress an array-bounds warning in GCC 12 by adding a compiler flag. It does not fix a bug but rather silences a warning.
The commit replaces pm_runtime_get_sync with pm_runtime_resume_and_get to simplify the code. It modifies the power management handling in the PRNG driver.

The commit involves refactoring code related to fixed file installation and removal in the io_uring subsystem. The main changes include moving functions to appropriate files and modifying function parameters to use context instead of kiocb.
The commit splits G1 and G2 nodes in media bindings, improving their independent management with proper power domains.
This commit removes the IWL_DEVICE_BZ_COMMON macro and modifies the IWL_DEVICE_BZ macro to include its contents. It appears to be a code cleanup or refactoring effort to consolidate definitions.
